NAME: KALAMAZOO COUNTY JAIL
PFAS_SOURCE: Sources of onsite pollution include waste dumped in a disposal pit; trichloroethene (TCE) used for cleaning and in a degreaser, floor drains, and other solvents dumped near the loading dock and in an onsite disposal pit. A release from a 2,500-gallon underground storage tank was reported in 1991. The contaminants detected in the soil and groundwater are volatile organic compounds, mainly the degreasing chemical TCE and associated degradation compounds. PFAS sampling was conducted by ELGE and their consultant due to the historical operations that may have involved PFAS coated or containing products and, known historical presence and migration of contaminants, and the close proximity of residential wells.
